

 * Pick a distribution

 * Design a configuration file, and a script to take those items and plop in the right places

 * Configure a syslog service

 * Configure SNMPv3

 * Document ways to get data into and out of the system.

 * Plan for what to do when space runs out 
    * Delete oldest stuff?
    * Start sending syslog out to another source?
    * Compress?
    * Stop logging ( to save the breakin data )
    * Send alerts?


